</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-39_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Before diving into the intricacies of adult BLS, it's crucial to understand the fundamental terms:
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-41_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-42_ pf-text-1"><strong>Cardiac arrest</strong> - The sudden cessation of heart function, leading to the loss of consciousness and absence of a pulse.













































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>Basic Life Support (BLS)</strong> - A set of interventions aimed at sustaining life in individuals experiencing cardiac arrest or respiratory failure until advanced medical help arrives.


























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-46_ pf-text-1"><strong>Chain of survival </strong>- A sequence of actions, including early recognition, prompt activation of emergency services, CPR, defibrillation, and advanced care, designed to improve survival rates in cardiac arrest cases.



























































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-48_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-49_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-50_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practice</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-52_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-53_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety (First Aid) Regulations 1981</strong> - Employers are legally obligated to provide adequate first aid provisions in the workplace, including training in BLS for designated first aiders.











































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-55_ pf-text-1"><strong>Resuscitation Council UK Guidelines 2021 </strong>-  The latest guidelines outline the recommended steps for performing high-quality BLS, including the importance of early recognition, effective chest compressions, and prompt defibrillation.























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-57_ pf-text-1"><strong>National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) Guidelines </strong>- NICE provides evidence-based recommendations for the management of cardiac arrest, emphasising the need for systematic approaches to BLS delivery.























































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-59_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-60_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-61_ pf-heading-1-h3">Early recognition and activation</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-63_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The first step in the chain of survival is recognising the signs of cardiac arrest and activating the emergency response system promptly.

</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-65_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-66_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-67_ pf-heading-1-h3">Effective chest compressions</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">High-quality chest compressions are the cornerstone of BLS, ensuring the circulation of oxygenated blood to vital organs.


</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-71_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-72_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-73_ pf-heading-1-h3">Airway management and rescue breaths</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-75_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Maintaining a patent airway and delivering rescue breaths can supplement chest compressions, optimising oxygen delivery to the lungs.



</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-77_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-78_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-79_ pf-heading-1-h3">Use of automated external defibrillators (AEDs)</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-81_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">AEDs play a crucial role in the early management of cardiac arrest. They can analyse heart rhythms and deliver shocks if indicated.




</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-83_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-84_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-85_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-87_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-88_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training and certification</strong> - Encourage individuals to undergo certified BLS training courses to equip themselves with the skills and confidence to respond effectively in emergencies.













































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-90_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular skills refresher</strong> - Skills degrade over time, so regular practice and refresher courses are essential to maintaining proficiency in BLS techniques.




























































